org.swerverobotics.library.interfaces

Class IBNO055IMU.Parameters

  • java.lang.Object
    • IBNO055IMU.Parameters
  • Enclosing interface:
    IBNO055IMU

    public static class IBNO055IMU.Parameters
extends java.lang.Object
    Instances of Parameters contain data indicating how a BNO055 absolute orientation sensor is to be initialized.
    See Also:
    IBNO055IMU.initialize(Parameters)

      • useExternalCrystal

        public boolean useExternalCrystal
        whether to use the external or internal 32.768khz crystal. External crystal use is recommended by the BNO055 specification.

      • temperatureUnit

        public IBNO055IMU.TEMPUNIT temperatureUnit
        units in which temperature are measured. See Section 3.6.1 (p31) of the BNO055 specification

      • angleunit

        public IBNO055IMU.ANGLEUNIT angleunit
        units in which angles and angular rates are measured. See Section 3.6.1 (p31) of the BNO055 specification

      • accelunit

        public IBNO055IMU.ACCELUNIT accelunit
        units in which accelerations are measured. See Section 3.6.1 (p31) of the BNO055 specification

      • pitchmode

        public IBNO055IMU.PITCHMODE pitchmode
        directional convention for measureing pitch angles. See Section 3.6.1 (p31) of the BNO055 specification

      • calibrationData

        public byte[] calibrationData
        calibration data with which the BNO055 should be initialized

      • accelerationIntegrationAlgorithm

        public IAccelerationIntegrator accelerationIntegrationAlgorithm
        the algorithm to use for integrating acceleration to produce velocity and position. If not specified, a simple but not especially effective internal algorithm will be used.

      • threadPriorityBoost

        public int threadPriorityBoost
        the boost in thread priority to use for data acquisition. A small increase in the thread priority can help reduce timestamping jitter and improve acceleration integration at only a small detriment to other parts of the system.

      • loggingEnabled

        public boolean loggingEnabled
        debugging aid: enable logging for this device?

        debugging aid: the logging tag to use when logging
